<paragraph id="8BE4E15A2A38F11DFF560EDD4E186CE9" blockId="16.[142,758,982,1218]" pageId="16" pageNumber="459">
<emphasis id="B92F3D482A38F11DFF560EDD4FA26BC0" box="[142,254,982,1003]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="459">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(only 
<specimenCount id="9D5D2AD32A38F11DFE970EDD4EE46BC7" box="[335,440,982,1004]" pageId="16" pageNumber="459" type="female">1 female</specimenCount>
): As for the ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B9AD92A38F11DFD8E0EDD4DE16BC0" authorityName="Bader" authorityYear="1988" box="[598,701,982,1003]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Synaptia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="16" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92F3D482A38F11DFD8E0EDD4DE16BC0" box="[598,701,982,1003]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="459">Synaptia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’-like species. Coxal field very short and blunt, anterior coxae (Cx-I/II) merely surpassing idiosoma, anterolaterally sharply graded; capitulum with short rostrum, separated from basal part of capitulum by sharp ventral and lateral bends; palp very characteristic, compact, especially P4 very short; P2/3 without ventral projections.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE4E15A2A38F11DFF5609EB4EB76CDD" blockId="16.[142,491,1248,1270]" box="[142,491,1248,1270]" pageId="16" pageNumber="459">
<emphasis id="B92F3D482A38F11DFF5609EB4E396CDE" box="[142,357,1248,1269]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="459">Description – Male</emphasis>
: Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE4E15A2A38F11DFF5608184EE26F5B" blockId="16.[142,758,1299,1904]" pageId="16" pageNumber="459">
<emphasis id="B92F3D482A38F11DFF5608184F836D03" box="[142,223,1299,1320]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="459">Female</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B92F3D482A38F11DFF2C081F4E546D02" box="[244,264,1300,1321]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="459">N</emphasis>
= 1): Idiosoma compact oval-shaped; dorsal plate reddish, antero-medial and antero-lateral platelets fused with dorsal plate; Dgl-4, lateral to Dgl-5 (
<figureCitation id="1360FDDF2A38F11DFF4E08644FAB6DAE" box="[150,247,1391,1413]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="15.[162,240,1854,1873]" captionTargetBox="[163,1440,493,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-152@15.[162,1442,492,1821]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 10. Torrenticola amalgamada. A–D, holotype female (CR 201). A, idiosoma, ventral view; B, idiosoma, dorsal view; C, capitulum with right palp, lateral view; D, chelicera, lateral view. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5432073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5432073/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="459">Fig. 10B</figureCitation>
); coxal field very short, blunt, merely protruding anterior margin of idiosoma; Cx-I/II and Cx-II/ III laterally sharply graded, antero-lateral corners of Cx-II and Cx-III pointing to anterior; Cxgl-4 far posterior, at margin of Cx-I and Cx-II, capitular bay wide U-shaped; posterior margin of Cx-IV far behind genital field; genital field large (gf L/Id L 0.25), broadrhombic, anteriorly rounded, laterally nearly straight, posteriorly tapering; excretory pore slightly posterior Vgl-2, pore and glands partly under caudal margin of primary sclerotization (
<figureCitation id="1360FDDF2A38F11DFE6B0BA94D496E93" box="[435,533,1698,1720]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="15.[162,240,1854,1873]" captionTargetBox="[163,1440,493,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-152@15.[162,1442,492,1821]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 10. Torrenticola amalgamada. A–D, holotype female (CR 201). A, idiosoma, ventral view; B, idiosoma, dorsal view; C, capitulum with right palp, lateral view; D, chelicera, lateral view. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5432073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5432073/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="459">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
); capitulum high, ventral margin with sharp bend towards short rostrum, separated by a sharp lateral ridge; palp very compact, especially P4 very short (L/H 1.18, P2/P4 2.00, P3/P4 1.15), P2/3 without ventral projections, ventral setae at P4 subterminal (
<figureCitation id="1360FDDF2A38F11DFDCF0A304D256F7A" box="[535,633,1851,1873]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="15.[162,240,1854,1873]" captionTargetBox="[163,1440,493,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-152@15.[162,1442,492,1821]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 10. Torrenticola amalgamada. A–D, holotype female (CR 201). A, idiosoma, ventral view; B, idiosoma, dorsal view; C, capitulum with right palp, lateral view; D, chelicera, lateral view. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5432073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5432073/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="459">Fig. 10C</figureCitation>
); chelicera relatively stout (
<figureCitation id="1360FDDF2A38F11DFE950A514EEE6F5B" box="[333,434,1882,1904]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="15.[162,240,1854,1873]" captionTargetBox="[163,1440,493,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-152@15.[162,1442,492,1821]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 10. Torrenticola amalgamada. A–D, holotype female (CR 201). A, idiosoma, ventral view; B, idiosoma, dorsal view; C, capitulum with right palp, lateral view; D, chelicera, lateral view. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5432073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5432073/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="459">Fig. 10D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE4E15A2A38F11DFCFE0E6D4B096F5B" blockId="16.[806,1422,870,1904]" pageId="16" pageNumber="459">
<emphasis id="B92F3D482A38F11DFCFE0E6D4CFC6B50" box="[806,928,870,891]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="459">Discussion</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B9AD92A38F11DFC6F0E6D4BB46B50" authorityName="Goldschmidt" authorityYear="2007" box="[951,1256,870,891]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Torrenticola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amalgamada">
<emphasis id="B92F3D482A38F11DFC6F0E6D4BB46B50" box="[951,1256,870,891]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="459">Torrenticola amalgamada</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is separated from all other species of the genus so far known, in the completely fused anterior platelets. This character is also found in several species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B9AD92A38F11DFAC00EC94C006BDE" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Pinquicola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="16" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Monatractides">
<emphasis id="B92F3D482A38F11DFAC00EC94C006BDE" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="459">Monatractides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B9AD92A38F11DFCB70EEA4B396BDE" authority="Cook, 1980" authorityName="Cook" authorityYear="1980" box="[879,1125,992,1014]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Megapalpis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="16" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gorda">
<emphasis id="B92F3D482A38F11DFCB70EEA4C896BDE" box="[879,981,992,1014]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="459">M. gorda</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCA9CAB2A38F11DFC3A0EEB4B396BDE" author="Cook DR" box="[994,1125,992,1014]" pageId="16" pageNumber="459" pagination="1 - 645" refId="ref111941" refString="Cook DR. 1980. Studies on Neotropical water mites. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute 31: 1 - 645." type="journal article" year="1980">Cook, 1980</bibRefCitation>
